parameters: alice
alice
Have both of you never seen a library before?
Just in case you haven’t know, my name is Patche.
\n<Patche>
Ah, pardon us. \n<Alice>
Miss Patche, we actually wanted to ask something.
What is it? \n<Patche>
Have you heard about some stolen grimoire? \n<Maris>
Well, there are many grimoires in this world,
it’s just a fancy name for books, to begin with.
Stolen books are like a common event since
ancient times. \n<Patche>
That's a dumb question, Maris. \n<Alice>
Damn, sorry! I was trying to help, too! \n<Maris>
We don’t really have that much clue...
But the only thing for sure that the said book was
taken by a lady who blinks away at instant after
talking to us. \n<Alice>
Blinking lady... Yukari? \n<Patchouli>
What did you know about her? \n<Maris>
She’s one of the sages that keeps this world’s balance.
If it’s Yukari’s doing, then whatever she did would
be something very important. \n<Patche>
My grimoire? Important? \n<Alice>
Could be. If my assumption is correct,
then the grimoire could be strongly correlated
with the peculiarity I found earlier... \n<Patche>
What kind of weirdness? \n<Maris>
For your information, aside from books, \n<Patche>
I also kept records of book pages that has lost
its sources.
Not long ago, when I regularly checked the \n<Patche>
record’s condition, one of the page somehow writes
itself, with no other papers doing the same thing...
Huh? Tell us more. \n<Alice>
I tried transcribing the writings in the pages.
Strange, it describes three different places
altogether. \n<Patche>
Damn, this is some prophecy crap. \n<Maris>
Not anymore since one of the place mentioned
in the page is the very location of this mansion.
\n<Patche>
Hmm, so, it’s safe to say that the places corresponds
with the location of the pages... \n<Alice>
Exactly. \n<Patche>
I like your deduction, Alice.
So... does it happen to also be able to grant wishes?
I kind of think this book may be able to do so.
\n<Maris>
That honestly sounds stupid. \n<Patche>
Any information regarding the other pages? \n<Alice>
The page states three places, as I repeat myself again.
\n<Patche>
First one is this mansion, the second one is said
to be “the mountain where wind rages”, \n<Patche>
and the last one is “the hell where demon lives”.
I would have fetched it before you arrive there.
That would also be when I’m not lazy enough.
\n<Patche>
You don’t have to be so cynical. \n<Maris>
It’s not even close to being cynical.
Do you even know what the word is? \n<Patche>
Oh Maris, do you really have to quarrel with everyone
all the way? \n<Alice>
We are sorry, Ms. Patche.
That is to be expected. \n<Patche>
About the mountain where wind rages,
where would it be? \n<Alice>
I suspect it wanted to say something about \n<Patche>
the Mountain of Faith, it is located just across
the vast sea that divides this world we live in.
How are we going to get there? \n<Maris>
Judging from your attire, I think an adventurer like
you should’ve knew. \n<Patche>
Just east from the port town, there’s a port
where you could sail all the way through.
Well then, Alice. It’s set! \n<Maris>
The mist is already gone, too.
Let’s embark our journey to the Mountain of Faith!
Okay, Maris. \n<Alice>
Ms. Patchouli, thank you for all the information!
\n<Alice>
Anytime. \n<Patche>
But, for two of you trying to get in Yukari’s plan,
that requires huge courage.
She took my friend away from me. \n<Maris>
I see... \n<Patche>
Must be good, having friends eh?
In that case, you should also go with us! \n<Maris>
Maris! \n<Alice>
Going out? With you? \n<Patche>
Are you putting jokes at times like this?
I’m too lazy to even come with you,
let alone facing the sage.
Pardon us, Ms. Patche. \n<Alice>
No matter. \n<Patche>
You know, if you need some clues regarding the script,
you are always free to come here so I can decode it
for you.
Why don’t you just come with us? \n<Maris>
It’s too much of a hassle to come from far away
just to get to this dank library-
Watch your mouth! Maybe this place is dark,
but it is always clean all the time! \n<Patche>
By Sakuya? \n<Alice>
It saves time. \n<Patche>
So, is it a yes or no? \n<Maris>
Do I have to repeat it myself that I don’t want to
join your band of misfit? \n<Patche>
Hey, the only misfit is him! \n<Alice>
I was just doing what’s need to be done.
Damn, I just wanted to help! Especially if the
grimoire containing some big power is true, \n<Maris>
then I am afraid if something bad happens to this
world and everyone I cared...
That’s unusually romantic coming out from
your rash mouth. \n<Alice>
Something bad, eh. \n<Patche>
I must admit, despite your hypothesis being stupid,
it is still possible that Yukari might be doing
something bad with it.
So, once again, is it a yes? \n<Maris>
$&#%, you don’t have to repeat it again.
My ears hurts. Yes! \n<Patche>
Alright! \n<Maris>
But first! \n<Patche>
Yeah? \n<Alice>
I have a task for both of you.
Come with me. \n<Patche>
To be continued....
